Diagnosis.
Body black (
Fig. 21
); eye in dorsal view 2.8 × as long as temple (
Fig. 22H
); eye in lateral view as high as wide (
Fig. 22J
); frons smooth posteriorly, but with some rugae near antennal sockets and densely granulate (
Fig. 22H
); vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 22H
); face 1.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially, densely granulate and with a medio-longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 22I
); clypeus small and semi-elliptical (
Fig. 22I
); precoxal sulcus widely crenulate, not reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 22B
); notauli sparsely crenulated and incomplete, impressed on disc (
Fig. 22C
); medio-posterior depression deep and crenulated, not extending to middle of mesoscutum (
Fig. 22C
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 22D
); pterostigma 4.0 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 22A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 22M
); length of first tergite 2.4 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae connected posteriorly (
Fig. 22D
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.4 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.4 times), and 1.3 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 22G
); antenna black (but scapus and annellus yellowish); mandible, pronope, metasoma (except first tergite black and posterior part of second to six tergite brownish) and legs (except hind tarsus, hind tibia and apical part of hind femur dark reddish brown) yellowish (
Fig. 21
).

Head. Transverse, width of head twice its lateral length, and 1.5 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 22H
); antenna with 39 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere5.0, 3.5 and 2.5 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 22F
); maxillary palp incomplete (
Fig. 21
); eye in dorsal view 2.8 × as long as temple (
Fig. 22H
); eye in lateral view as high as wide (
Fig. 22J
); frons smooth posteriorly, but with some rugae near antennal sockets and densely granulate (
Fig. 22H
); vertex and temple smooth; OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 11:5:4; face 1.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially, densely granulate and with a medio-longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 22I
); clypeus small and semi-elliptical (
Fig. 22I
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 22K
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobeshaped (
Fig. 22L
), ventral carina protruding, middle tooth curved and acute, with no incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 22K
), medial length of mandible 1.6 × its maximum width.

